---
layout: layout.njk
title: Democratic Justice — Proof. Not Spin.
description: Proof. Not spin. Democratic Justice equips West Virginia Democrats with verified election integrity proofs, secure submission guidance, and action resources.
reviewDate: 2024-12-01
---

{% set featuredCases = collections.caseStudies | slice(0, 3) %}
{% set totalProofs = collections.sortedProofs | length %}

<header class="hero" role="banner">
  <div class="align-container">
    <div class="hero-grid hero-grid--single">
      <div>
        <h1 class="hero-headline">Proof.<strong>Not Spin.</strong></h1>
        <p class="hero-lede">We assemble sworn records into proof the stronger party can’t ignore—and put it in your hands so you can demand accountability.</p>
        <div class="btn-group">
          <a href="{{ '/overproofs/' | url }}" class="btn btn-accent">
            Explore Overproofs
          </a>
          <a href="{{ '/action' | url }}" class="btn btn-outline-white">
            Take Action
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

{% set latestProof = collections.sortedProofs | last %}
{% if latestProof and latestProof.overproof %}
  {% set latestOverproof = latestProof.overproof %}
  {% set latestProofSlug = (latestProof.slug or latestProof.case_id) | slug %}
  {% set latestProofUrl = ('/proofs/' ~ latestOverproof.slug ~ '/' ~ latestProofSlug ~ '/') | url %}
  {% set latestCaseUrl = (latestOverproof.url or ('/briefs/' ~ latestOverproof.slug ~ '/')) | url %}
  {% set latestCaseTitle = latestOverproof.short_title or latestOverproof.title %}
<section class="latest-proof" aria-labelledby="latest-proof-heading">
  <div class="align-container">
    <article class="latest-proof__card">
      <header class="latest-proof__header">
        <p class="section-label">Latest Proof</p>
        <h2 id="latest-proof-heading">Proof {{ latestProof.case_id }} — {{ latestProof.title }}</h2>
        <p class="latest-proof__summary">{{ latestProof.thesis }}</p>
      </header>

      <div class="latest-proof__grid">
        <dl class="latest-proof__meta">
          <div>
            <dt>Case Brief</dt>
            <dd><a href="{{ latestCaseUrl }}">{{ latestCaseTitle }}</a></dd>
          </div>
          {% if latestProof.date %}
          <div>
            <dt>Filed</dt>
            <dd>{{ latestProof.date | date }}</dd>
          </div>
          {% endif %}
          {% if latestProof.category %}
          <div>
            <dt>Category</dt>
            <dd>{{ latestProof.category }}</dd>
          </div>
          {% endif %}
        </dl>

        <div class="latest-proof__detail">
          {% if latestProof.violation %}
          <h3>Violation</h3>
          <p>{{ latestProof.violation | safe }}</p>
          {% endif %}
          {% if latestProof.stakes %}
          <h3>Stakes</h3>
          <p>{{ latestProof.stakes | safe }}</p>
          {% endif %}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="latest-proof__actions">
        <a href="{{ latestProofUrl }}" class="btn btn-accent">Examine Proof</a>
        <a href="{{ latestCaseUrl }}" class="btn btn-outline-blue">View Case Brief</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

{% if featuredCases and featuredCases | length %}
<section class="key-cases" id="key-cases" aria-labelledby="key-cases-heading">
  <div class="align-container">
    <p class="section-label">Investigative Briefs</p>
    <h2 id="key-cases-heading">Key Cases</h2>
    <p class="lead">Start with the major violations our research has proven. Each case brief connects the documents, testimony, and rulings into a clear narrative.</p>

    <div class="key-case-grid">
      {% for study in featuredCases %}
        {% set overproofGroup = study.data.overproofGroup %}
        {% set overproof = overproofGroup.overproof %}
        {% set brief = overproof.brief %}
        {% set caseTitle = (brief and brief.headline) or overproof.short_title or overproof.title %}
        {% set caseSummary = study.data.description or (brief and brief.lede) or overproof.summary %}
        {% set proofCount = overproof.proofCount or (overproofGroup.proofs | length) %}
        <article class="key-case-card">
          {% if overproof.umbrella_category %}
          <p class="key-case-card__kicker">VIOLATION: {{ overproof.umbrella_category }}</p>
          {% endif %}
          <h3><a href="{{ study.url | url }}">{{ caseTitle }}</a></h3>
          {% if caseSummary %}
          <p class="key-case-card__summary">{{ caseSummary | truncate(210) }}</p>
          {% endif %}
          <div class="key-case-card__meta">
            {% if proofCount %}
            <span>{{ proofCount }} documented proofs</span>
            {% endif %}
            {% if overproof.metadata and overproof.metadata.Timeframe %}
            <span>{{ overproof.metadata.Timeframe }}</span>
            {% endif %}
          </div>
          <a class="key-case-card__cta" href="{{ study.url | url }}">Read case brief →</a>
        </article>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>

    <div class="key-case-actions">
      <a href="{{ '/overproofs/' | url }}" class="btn btn-outline-blue">View all case briefs</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

{% set caseStudies = collections.caseStudies %}
{% if caseStudies and caseStudies | length %}
<section class="case-files" id="case-files" aria-labelledby="case-files-heading">
  <div class="align-container">
    <p class="section-label">Case Files</p>
    <h2 id="case-files-heading">Case Brief Archive</h2>
    <p class="lead">Browse every active case file to understand how the documented proofs come together.</p>

    {% include "case-study-list.njk" with { studies: caseStudies } %}
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

<section class="method" id="method" aria-labelledby="method-heading">
  <div class="align-container">
    <p class="section-label">How We Prove It</p>
    <h2 id="method-heading">Four Steps. Clear Proof.</h2>
    <div class="method-single-box">
      <div class="method-single-box__header">
        <h3>FOUR-STEP PROOF</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="method-single-box__item">
        <p class="method-step-number">1. AXIOM</p>
        <p class="method-step-description">Quote the rule or premise.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="method-single-box__item">
        <p class="method-step-number">2. EVIDENCE</p>
        <p class="method-step-description">Show the record. Cite the document.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="method-single-box__item">
        <p class="method-step-number">3. REASONING &mdash; THE PROOF</p>
        <p class="method-step-description">Derive the claim from 1 &amp; 2.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="method-single-box__item">
        <p class="method-step-number">4. CONCLUSION (Q.E.D.)</p>
        <p class="method-step-description">State the claim proven and the remedy.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="archive-cta" aria-labelledby="archive-cta-heading">
  <div class="align-container">
    <div class="archive-cta__card">
      <h2 id="archive-cta-heading">Dig into the full evidence locker</h2>
      <p>Ready to examine every document for yourself? Explore the complete archive of {{ totalProofs }} vetted proofs, including source citations and filings.</p>
      <a href="{{ '/archive' | url }}" class="btn btn-outline-blue">Explore the full proof archive</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="action" id="action" aria-labelledby="action-heading">
  <div class="align-container">
    <h2 id="action-heading">
      Proof {% image "/images/three-dots-gold.svg", "Therefore symbol", {
        class: "mark md",
        widths: [24, 48],
        sizes: "24px",
        style: "transform: translateY(0.1em);",
        ariaHidden: true
      } %} Action
    </h2>
    <div class="action-card">
      <p>Turn proofs into formal challenges. Start with a challenge review—if your case qualifies, we can stay with you through filing.</p>
      <ul class="action-list">
        <li>Challenge review confirming standing, deadlines, and required evidence</li>
        <li>Written recommendations with board citations and filing steps</li>
        <li>Optional end-to-end challenge support for qualifying cases</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="btn-group">
        <a href="{{ '/action' | url }}" class="btn btn-outline-blue">Explore Support</a>
        <a href="{{ '/action/file' | url }}" class="btn btn-accent">Request a Review</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="cta-section" id="cta" aria-labelledby="cta-heading">
  <div class="align-container">
    <h2 id="cta-heading">Submit Proof</h2>
    <p>Have documents or testimony? Share it securely and confidentially.</p>

    <form id="secure-contact" name="secure-contact" method="POST" netlify netlify-honeypot="bot-field" class="cta-form">
      <input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="secure-contact">
      <p class="visually-hidden"><label>Leave this empty <input name="bot-field"></label></p>

      <label for="email" class="visually-hidden">Your email for secure contact</label>
      <input type="email" id="email" name="email" placeholder="your@email.com" required>

      <label for="message" class="visually-hidden">Your message</label>
      <textarea id="message" name="message" placeholder="Briefly describe the proof you have..." rows="4" required></textarea>

      <button type="submit">Contact Me</button>
    </form>

    <p id="cta-error">Sorry—something went wrong. Email <a href="mailto:setho@democraticjustice.org">setho@democraticjustice.org</a>.</p>

    <p style="font-size:13px;margin-top:16px;opacity:.9"><strong>Note:</strong> Don't send documents via this form. We'll arrange a secure transfer.</p>
  </div>
</section>
